a thousand times in my mind,</i>

01:13.324 --> 01:14.826
<i>but I never actually
went anywhere.</i>

01:17.495 --> 01:18.705
<i>What was the final straw?</i>

01:20.331 --> 01:21.666
<i>I had nothing.</i>

01:23.668 --> 01:25.170
<i>There's the unsupportive family.</i>

01:25.920 --> 01:28.131
No, I don't give a crap
if that's what she wants.

01:28.214 --> 01:31.092
She's not gonna sit in my
goddamn house and do nothing!

01:32.969 --> 01:34.179
MEGAN: <i>The dead-end job.</i>

01:34.596 --> 01:36.931
<i>Jungle Ru went up and down</i>

01:37.015 --> 01:39.225
<i>On a big adventure</i>

01:39.309 --> 01:42.145
MEGAN: <i>Then getting fired from the
dead-end job for being hungover.</i>

01:42.562 --> 01:43.605
Yeah...

01:44.689 --> 01:46.441
This isn't working.
I get it.

01:46.524 --> 01:50.236
Megan, it's just, you don't really
connect with people very well.

01:50.570 --> 01:52.047
I'm sorry to be the one
to tell you this.

01:52.071 --> 01:53.448
No, no, no, it's fine.

01:54.491 --> 01:55.575
Really.

01:56.868 --> 01:57.869
(BELL JANGLES)

02:02.540 --> 02:05.460
MEGAN: <i>In the end, you don't leave
because you have somewhere to go.</i>

02:07.253 --> 02:09.293
<i>You leave because there's
nothing keeping you there.</i>

02:26.856 --> 02:28.900
<i>All I know is that
after my best friend died,</i>

02:30.151 --> 02:31.511
<i>there was nothing
left for me here.</i>

02:33.404 --> 02:35.240
<i>I checked out of
life completely.</i>

02:38.868 --> 02:41.996
<i>And I realized if
I didn't leave now,</i>

02:42.080 --> 02:43.790
<i>I wasn't gonna
be far behind him.</i>

02:47.418 --> 02:48.711
(HORN HONKS)

02:57.053 --> 03:00.139
