MUSIC PLAYING)

03:00.849 --> 03:02.767
ANNOUNCER: <i>Due to heightened
security measures,</i>

03:02.934 --> 03:04.853
<i>please keep bags
with you at all times.</i>

03:04.936 --> 03:07.939
<i>All unaccompanied luggage
will be confiscated.</i>

03:34.299 --> 03:35.842
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

03:37.927 --> 03:39.178
Hello?
JACKIE: <i>Yeah.</i>

03:39.262 --> 03:43.600
Uh, what is this pamphlet for the
Marines that I found in your dresser?

03:43.683 --> 03:46.120
I think there's some pot left in the
sock drawer if you keep digging.

03:46.144 --> 03:47.979
Yeah, don't be a wise ass,
this is my house.

03:48.438 --> 03:50.899
And just so you know, running
away isn't gonna solve anything,

03:50.982 --> 03:53.222
<i>'cause that's all you've ever done...</i>
Hang up that phone!

03:53.276 --> 03:54.402
FEMALE MARINE: Let's go!

03:54.485 --> 03:57.113
MALE MARINE:
Let's go, move, move, move.

03:57.405 --> 04:00.575
Let's go, faster,
come on, move, move.

04:01.159 --> 04:02.911
Tuck in that shirt!
My shirt?

04:02.994 --> 04:04.579
Tuck your shirt in!

04:05.079 --> 04:06.331
Fix your hair!

04:06.831 --> 04:09.125
Get in line, move!
Let's go, move.

04:09.208 --> 04:11.544
You have taken the first
step in becoming a member

04:11.628 --> 04:13.338
of the world's
finest fighting force,

04:13.421 --> 04:15.006
the United States Marine Corps.

04:15.340 --> 04:18.259
Tens of thousands of Marines
have begun outstanding service

04:18.343 --> 04:20.261
for our country
starting right here.

04:20.845 --> 04:24.098
You will continue that proud tradition.
Do you understand?

04:24.349 --> 04:25.475
ALL: Aye-aye, sir!

04:25.558 --> 04:26.601
