17:34.972 --> 17:36.572
COLETTA: <i>So, you want us
to run it again?</i>

17:36.849 --> 17:39.130
GUNNY: <i>So we gonna keep running
this till we get it right.</i>

17:39.643 --> 17:40.963
<i>You're gonna save
lives out there.</i>

17:42.187 --> 17:44.749
SPORTS ANNOUNCER: <i>And the Red Sox
come pouring out of their dugout,</i>

17:44.773 --> 17:46.066
<i>the Yankees out of theirs.</i>

17:46.150 --> 17:49.194
<i>They've all met out near the
pitcher's mound in a scrum.</i>

17:50.112 --> 17:51.321
<i>Meanwhile...</i>

17:51.405 --> 17:52.823
(PANTING)

17:58.370 --> 18:00.581
Why does your run
always seem to end up here?

18:02.291 --> 18:03.500
Does it?
I hadn't noticed.

18:05.502 --> 18:07.254
Hey, I've got a PFT
in a couple of weeks.

18:07.337 --> 18:08.380
Just wondering,

18:08.797 --> 18:10.090
you got any openings
coming up?

18:17.055 --> 18:18.390
(SIGHS)

18:18.474 --> 18:19.767
Good talk.

18:19.850 --> 18:21.995
ANNOUNCER: <i>Out of the gate,
there's a fly ball deep to left,</i>

18:22.019 --> 18:24.104
<i>it's on its way,
there it goes,</i>

18:24.188 --> 18:26.732
<i>and the Yankees are going
to the World Series!</i>

18:27.608 --> 18:29.651
(ALL BREATHING HEAVILY)

18:35.824 --> 18:39.369
SHOOTING INSTRUCTOR: Cease fire,
cease fire, unload, all clear.

18:39.912 --> 18:42.247
Shooters, your prep time
has ended

18:42.331 --> 18:44.333
with a magazine
of five rounds.

18:45.501 --> 18:46.981
MASON: I finished
the morning reports.

18:47.377 --> 18:48.754
I need
the trainer's schedule, too.

18:48.837 --> 18:50.380
When do you need it by?
1400.

18:50.589 --> 18:51.799
On it, Gunny.
Enter.

18:55.093 --> 18:56.428
PFC Leavey,

18:56.512 --> 18:58.722
why am I not surprised
to see you in here today?

19:01.099 --> 19:04.228
Yeah, I heard you got
first class on your PFT,

19:04.895 --> 19:06.063
and you shot expert.

19:06.814 --> 19:08.732
Gunny, do you have a dog for me?
No.

19:10.275 --> 19:11.527
Did I excuse you?

19:15.113 --> 19:16.698
But I do got a can, though.

19:18.367 --> 19:19.576
What you say there, Mason?

19:20.244 --> 19:21.495
Think she ready for a can?

19:22.788 --> 19:24.122
I think so, Gunny.

19:24.414 --> 19:25.624
(CHUCKLES)

19:26.416 --> 19:27.543
Carry on.

19:29.253 --> 19:30.712
MEGAN: Let's get to work.

19:30.921 --> 19:32.422
(PANTING)

19:38.220 --> 19:39.388
Hey, cute dog.

19:40.347 --> 19:41.431
What's his name?

19:42.140 --> 19:43.475
I mean, her name.

19:43.600 --> 19:44.601
(ALL LAUGH)

19:44.935 --> 19:47.271
I haven't named her yet,
I'm waiting for us to bond.

19:47.896 --> 19:49.606
Don't forgot to use
your praise voice.

19:49.690 --> 19:51.567
(IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE)
Good can, good can.

19:51.650 --> 19:53.443
At least my can
listens to me.

19:54.236 --> 19:57.114
Hey, she listens to me.
You listen to me, right, baby?

19:57.573 --> 19:59.032
Come on, come on.

19:59.116 --> 20:00.492
SILLS: You hear that?

20:00.784 --> 20:01.785
Huh?

20:01.869 --> 20:03.412
Come on.
You hear that?

20:06.123 --> 20:07.123
Morning.

20:07.165 --> 20:08.292
ALL: Morning, Gunny.

20:09.376 --> 20:11.128
Any DUIs last night?

20:11.712 --> 20:12.880
ALL: No, Gunny.

20:12.963 --> 20:15.340
Good.
It's gonna be a good day.

20:16.133 --> 20:18.135
We gonna train
harder than ever before.

20:19.845 --> 20:21.471
Walters, what was
you doing last night?

20:21.972 --> 20:23.181
Playing <i>Halo,</i> Gunny.

20:23.265 --> 20:24.516
That's what you do
all the time?

20:24.600 --> 20:26.059
You shipping out
in three weeks.

20:26.143 --> 20:28.937
You better be ready to fight
when it's time to fight.

20:30.355 --> 20:31.940
Mason.
Yes, Gunny.

20:32.024 --> 20:33.150
Are you still a virgin?

20:34.234 --> 20:35.360
No, Gunny.

20:35.444 --> 20:37.446
Are you sure about that?
Because you look like one.

20:40.991 --> 20:42.677
Bennett, did you talk
to your wife last night?

20:42.701 --> 20:44.161
No, Gunny.
You think I give a damn?

20:46.705 --> 20:49.166
Coletta, you wipe that smile
off your face. Yes, Gunny.

20:49.833 --> 20:50.959
Now, on a serious note,

20:51.043 --> 20:53.378
I have somebody that
just came back from Iraq.

20:54.004 --> 20:56.089
He wants to talk to y'all
about the experience,

20:57.174 --> 20:58.342
so you'll know what it is.

20:58.967 --> 21:00.385
He's been where you're going,

21:00.469 --> 21:03.597
and the things that he
tells you will save lives

21:03.680 --> 21:04.848
and save limbs.

21:06.183 --> 21:07.684
This is Sergeant Andrew Dean.

21:08.602 --> 21:10.437
Sergeant, take the floor.
Thank you, Gunny.

21:13.482 --> 21:15.525
Morning.
ALL: Morning, Sergeant.

21:16.360 --> 21:17.569
Are you ready for war?

21:17.653 --> 21:18.946
ALL: Yes, Sergeant.

21:19.404 --> 21:20.864
Everything
you've prepared for,

21:21.907 --> 21:23.033
every lesson
you've learnt,

21:24.826 --> 21:26.370
everything you think
you know

21:27.537 --> 21:30.040
will just go to shit
the moment you're in country.

21:30.582 --> 21:32.167
These homemade bombs
are full of crap

21:32.250 --> 21:34.002
that our dogs
have never sniffed.

21:36.672 --> 21:40.717
You get caught in a sandstorm,
the dogs will be confused,

21:41.551 --> 21:43.431
and they won't be able
to detect the odor cones.

21:44.721 --> 21:48.392
You're about to be running
through shit's creek, literally.

21:50.686 --> 21:52.562
With 50 pounds on your back,

21:53.563 --> 21:54.815
a dog on a leash,

21:55.565 --> 21:57.818
trying not to smack
his head in with your rifle.

22:00.237 --> 22:01.717
And the grunts that
you're protecting?

22:04.408 --> 22:06.288
Well, they'll pretty much
hate you from day one.

22:08.078 --> 22:10.205
Do this job right,
you might save lives.

22:11.415 --> 22:13.709
Do it wrong,
and you'll wind up dead.

22:16.878 --> 22:19.172
And no matter how bad
I'm making it sound,

22:20.090 --> 22:21.591
I'm not even coming close.

22:25.804 --> 22:27.389
(DOGS BARKING)

22:29.099 --> 22:30.559
VET: You need to
keep them calm.

22:33.270 --> 22:34.855
Lie down, Rex, lie down.

22:34.938 --> 22:36.440
That's looking good.

22:37.566 --> 22:38.900
Down.
That's looking good.

22:40.485 --> 22:42.988
Just pull so there are
no wrinkles in the gauze.

22:43.488 --> 22:46.074
You need to practice
all of this before you deploy.

22:47.784 --> 22:49.578
Okay, let's take off
the leashes.

22:52.080 --> 22:54.041
Rex, no, no.

22:54.750 --> 22:56.102
Are you having
a problem over there?

22:56.126 --> 22:57.377
No, I got this.

22:58.545 --> 22:59.713
Good boy.

23:01.256 --> 23:03.175
I said take off the leash.

23:04.468 --> 23:06.428
Come on, buddy, just relax.
(SNARLS)

23:07.345 --> 23:09.139
Good boy, just relax.

23:09.222 --> 23:11.224
You need to muzzle
that dog now.

23:12.809 --> 23:13.810
WALTERS: Ahh!

23:14.019 --> 23:15.020
(GRUNTING)

23:15.604 --> 23:16.730
Bad dog!

23:18.148 --> 23:19.149
Shit.

23:19.691 --> 23:21.234
It's gonna happen
when it happens.

23:21.318 --> 23:23.296
Gunny, I'm telling you,
it's gonna heal in no time.

23:23.320 --> 23:25.238
He broke six bones,
Walters.

23:25.489 --> 23:26.615
You wanted to see me,
Gunny?

23:27.240 --> 23:28.408
You're getting a dog.

23:28.492 --> 23:29.576
What?

23:29.659 --> 23:30.702
You're giving her my dog.

23:30.786 --> 23:32.079
Wait.
He's not your dog.

23:32.162 --> 23:34.081
He's not my dog.
He's a Marine Corps dog.

23:34.164 --> 23:35.707
Rex needs
an experienced handler.

23:35.791 --> 23:37.560
Are you questioning
my authority, Lance Corporal?

23:37.584 --> 23:39.544
She's a Boot. She's
only trained a can so far.

23:39.628 --> 23:42.005
Quit whining and act
like a goddamn Marine.

23:42.506 --> 23:43.673
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

23:46.968 --> 23:48.970
You got this?
Think faster.

23:49.054 --> 23:50.138
Yeah, I got this.

23:50.514 --> 23:52.015
Good, you're dismissed.

24:17.165 --> 24:18.667
Remember me?

24:21.253 --> 24:22.546
(SIGHS)

24:23.004 --> 24:25.507
All right, Rex,
get in the house.

24:30.387 --> 24:31.555
In the house, now.

24:31.972 --> 24:34.092
You're not gonna get any food
unless you listen to me.

24:37.769 --> 24:40.647
I will stand here
all day, okay?

24:56.329 --> 24:57.455
Yes.

24:58.206 --> 24:59.791
Good, good.

25:00.584 --> 25:02.043
Good boy, stay.

25:02.752 --> 25:03.920
Stay.

25:17.475 --> 25:18.935
MEGAN: Over here, seek.

25:20.353 --> 25:22.272
Seek, seek.

25:24.274 --> 25:25.483
Seek.

25:26.568 --> 25:27.903
That's time, Leavey.
(SIGHS)

25:28.945 --> 25:30.238
Damn it.

25:36.828 --> 25:38.455
You found one
out of five.

25:38.955 --> 25:40.040
See this guy?

25:40.123 --> 25:43.543
Dead, dead, dead.

25:43.627 --> 25:45.587
Oh, and your dog,
yeah, he's dead, too.

25:46.963 --> 25:48.965
And you blew off your
legs in the process.

25:49.049 --> 25:50.300
Follow me.

25:53.136 --> 25:54.387
Again, Leavey.

25:55.347 --> 25:57.557
MEGAN: Hey, hey. Hey.

25:57.641 --> 25:58.681
DEAN: Where are you going?

25:58.975 --> 26:00.912
Following the perimeter.
He's pulling towards the desk.

26:00.936 --> 26:02.371
But I thought there
was a search pattern.

26:02.395 --> 26:04.189
Forget the search pattern,
Leavey.

26:05.106 --> 26:06.650
He's showing a change,
all right?

26:06.733 --> 26:08.193
Listen to him.
Okay.

26:08.276 --> 26:10.111
Rex, seek.
Follow him.

26:10.195 --> 26:11.321
Okay, seek.

26:18.453 --> 26:20.830
That's it, that's it.
He's on odor, present higher.

26:32.509 --> 26:33.927
Praise him, Leavey,
praise him.

26:34.010 --> 26:36.846
Good boy, good boy, good.

26:38.682 --> 26:40.684
Okay, this is a
good detection dog.

26:41.184 --> 26:42.519
There's nothing
wrong with him,

26:43.019 --> 26:44.354
so it must be you.

26:45.397 --> 26:46.815
What are you
doing wrong?

26:47.732 --> 26:50.819
Everything you feel
goes down leash, okay?

26:50.902 --> 26:51.987
Everything.

26:52.904 --> 26:54.824
If you're not confident,
then he's not confident.

26:56.533 --> 26:58.576
I could train the heck
out of you, Leavey, but...

27:00.036 --> 27:03.206
I can't teach you
how to bond, okay?

27:03.957 --> 27:04.958
Okay.

27:05.667 --> 27:06.876
Good work.

27:15.385 --> 27:16.594
(BARKING)

27:16.678 --> 27:18.096
Okay, he's just nervous.

27:18.847 --> 27:19.973
These aren't nerves.

27:20.056 --> 27:21.057
Shh!

27:21.141 --> 27:22.726
I've been watching
this dog all year.

27:23.059 --> 27:25.145
He's the most aggressive dog
I've ever treated.

27:27.397 --> 27:29.566
He can't deploy without this exam.
Hey!

27:30.108 --> 27:31.776
I'll have to sedate him.
(SHUSHING)

27:35.572 --> 27:38.033
Rex, calm down, calm down.

27:38.825 --> 27:39.868
Come on.

27:42.746 --> 27:44.664
This door always
stays closed, okay?

27:45.415 --> 27:47.542
Hey, Alice, Tucker.

27:48.585 --> 27:50.086
All right,
go find Walters

27:50.170 --> 27:51.689
and tell him I want Tucker's
cleaned out again.

27:51.713 --> 27:52.756
Yes, Sergeant.

27:53.048 --> 27:55.050
Hey, good girl.

27:56.801 --> 28:00.221
Leavey, wrap his leg.
Show him you're not afraid.

28:00.764 --> 28:01.765
Yes, Sergeant.

28:03.767 --> 28:04.768
(SIGHS)

28:06.436 --> 28:07.979
Rex, sit. I mean...

28:09.105 --> 28:10.148
Lay down.

28:11.566 --> 28:12.734
Rex, lay down.

28:21.743 --> 28:22.952
Stay.

28:28.291 --> 28:29.793
I'm just gonna wrap your paw.

28:37.717 --> 28:38.718
Just...

28:39.344 --> 28:40.470
Here you go.

28:42.180 --> 28:43.681
Good, good.

28:47.102 --> 28:48.162
If you ever get
into trouble,

28:48.186 --> 28:49.906
you're gonna want me
to know how to do this.

28:53.817 --> 28:55.110
Hey.

28:57.362 --> 28:58.571
I didn't...

28:59.447 --> 29:00.782
I didn't ask for Rex.

29:01.282 --> 29:02.450
I didn't even want him.

29:04.327 --> 29:05.662
Yeah, well,
I did want him.

29:07.205 --> 29:08.540
So, don't get him killed.

29:12.127 --> 29:13.586
(GATE CLANGS)

29:42.198 --> 29:43.199
(SOFTLY) Hey.

29:44.576 --> 29:45.577
Hey.

30:03.261 --> 30:04.721
Rex, sit.

30:07.056 --> 30:08.391
Oh, good.

30:22.280 --> 30:23.948
We're shipping out tomorrow.

30:26.075 --> 30:27.744
We are so not ready for this.

30:30.747 --> 30:34.459
But people are counting on us,

30:34.542 --> 30:39.088
and if we do it wrong,
people die, so we gotta do it right.

30:41.799 --> 30:42.967
Okay?

30:56.231 --> 30:59.692
GUNNY: <i>Tomorrow, beginning the
moment you step off that bird,</i>

30:59.776 --> 31:02.529
<i>you must act,
trust your training,</i>

31:02.987 --> 31:05.615
<i>trust your partner,
trust yourself.</i>

31:05.740 --> 31:06.741
ALL: Hoo-ah!

31:07.283 --> 31:08.493
GUNNY: <i>And remember,</i>

31:08.576 --> 31:11.871
<i>everything you see,
hear, taste, and touch</i>

31:11.955 --> 31:13.540
<i>over these next seven months</i>

31:14.165 --> 31:16.376
<i>will remain with you for
the rest of your lives.</i>

31:16.960 --> 31:18.127
<i>Make it count.</i>

31:22.173 --> 31:23.424
You okay, Leavey?

31:24.634 --> 31:26.219
Yeah, I just can't find
my Ka-Bar.

31:26.636 --> 31:28.516
It was in my stuff and now I...
It's behind you.

31:29.973 --> 31:31.349
(SIGHS)

31:31.432 --> 31:32.642
Thank you.

31:32.976 --> 31:35.311
Look, it's okay to be freaking
out right now, all right?

31:35.395 --> 31:36.563
It's normal.

31:36.646 --> 31:38.398
I did, everybody does.

31:39.190 --> 31:40.483
You'll be fine.

31:40.900 --> 31:41.901
You got this.

31:41.985 --> 31:43.825
And I wanna hear about
all the asses you kicked

31:43.903 --> 31:45.029
when you come back.

31:45.113 --> 31:47.115
Not if, but when, okay?

31:47.198 --> 31:48.241
Okay.

31:52.620 --> 31:53.830
Good luck.

31:54.330 --> 31:55.331
Thank you.

32:08.219 --> 32:10.263
(REX BARKING)

32:10.346 --> 32:12.807
Rex, shh, quiet,
you're fine.

32:12.890 --> 32:16.394
Hour of silence, Leavey.
I'll settle for 30 minutes.

32:16.477 --> 32:17.604
I'm sorry.

32:32.535 --> 32:33.995
It works for birds.

32:35.955 --> 32:36.956
(CHUCKLES)

32:37.040 --> 32:38.791
(SHUSHING)

32:38.875 --> 32:40.293
Hey, I know.

32:40.376 --> 32:42.587
Hey, it's okay, I know.

32:43.713 --> 32:44.857
You don't know
where we're going

32:44.881 --> 32:46.549
or what's gonna happen
when we get there.

32:47.884 --> 32:50.303
I know it sucks, but we're
in this together, okay?

32:51.220 --> 32:52.263
(SHUSHES)

32:52.347 --> 32:54.891
It's okay. It's okay,
buddy, I got you.

33:09.072 --> 33:11.407
We're on final,
be on the ground in 10.

33:11.532 --> 33:14.410
Get your gear together, strap in.
Get ready for landing.

33:15.411 --> 33:16.829
(MARINES WHOOPING)
All right.

33:18.289 --> 33:21.125
Okay, listen up.
Where's Marion and Peters?

33:21.209 --> 33:22.209
Sir.

33:22.251 --> 33:23.628
Your vehicles are
right over there.

33:23.711 --> 33:25.254
You're going to
Camp Perditha.

33:25.338 --> 33:26.673
Leavey, Jones.
Yeah.

33:27.256 --> 33:28.651
Your convoy's waiting for you
right over there.

33:28.675 --> 33:30.527
You're going to Camp Ramadi.
The rest of you, follow me.

33:30.551 --> 33:32.637
Hey, don't forget,
no matter how bad it gets,

33:33.471 --> 33:35.831
you could have been out there
sniffing bombs with a tin can.

33:36.766 --> 33:38.059
(CHUCKLES) True.

33:38.476 --> 33:39.519
(CHUCKLES) Be safe.

33:39.602 --> 33:41.270
Okay.
All right?

33:41.938 --> 33:43.106
Hey, good hunting.

33:44.107 --> 33:45.566
See you later, idiots.

33:45.775 --> 33:47.860
MARINE: <i>Adios!</i> (BARKS)

34:15.763 --> 34:17.223
At least we got
a single, right?

34:17.806 --> 34:19.141
(DISTANT EXPLOSION)

34:20.393 --> 34:22.687
Sometimes it actually
pays to be a girl.

34:24.105 --> 34:25.106
(WHIMPERING)

34:32.155 --> 34:33.322
(DISTANT EXPLOSION)

34:33.406 --> 34:34.741
(REX WHIMPERS)

34:37.784 --> 34:39.161
Don't be scared.

34:44.876 --> 34:46.627
(RUSTLING)

34:52.007 --> 34:53.009
Hey.

34:53.842 --> 34:54.844
(CHUCKLES)

34:55.678 --> 34:56.888
Oh, great.

34:57.764 --> 35:00.349
You wait to get to Iraq
to find your inner puppy.

35:01.058 --> 35:02.685
(LAUGHS)

35:09.525 --> 35:11.819
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

35:38.888 --> 35:41.098
MORALES: (TUTTING)
Up, up, up, up.

35:41.724 --> 35:43.267
Good boy, good boy.

35:43.351 --> 35:45.686
Yes, that's a good boy,
good boy.

35:46.687 --> 35:49.398
Oh, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah.

35:50.566 --> 35:53.319
Good boy, good boy,
yeah, yeah.

35:53.402 --> 35:54.570
(DISTANT EXPLOSION)

35:55.988 --> 35:57.240
That's a good boy.

35:57.907 --> 35:59.075
Relax, Boot.

35:59.367 --> 36:00.827
It's outgoing, not incoming.

36:02.370 --> 36:03.496
Ain't that right,
Chico, huh?

36:03.704 --> 36:04.747
Thanks.

36:05.498 --> 36:08.584
Yeah, yeah.

36:25.601 --> 36:26.727
Settle down.
Come on, man.

36:26.811 --> 36:27.979
Let's go.

36:28.062 --> 36:29.188
Yeah, move it along.

36:29.272 --> 36:30.648
Hurry it up, all right?

36:47.582 --> 36:48.958
First day of school, bud.

36:51.878 --> 36:53.045
Wish me luck.

37:02.847 --> 37:04.847
I'm pretty sure they sell
loofahs in the gift shop.

37:05.474 --> 37:07.518
Actually, no,
they bombed the gift shop.

37:08.144 --> 37:10.021
Well, that's too bad.
I like loofahs.

37:11.230 --> 37:13.691
I'm Matt Morales.
I'll be your tour guide today.

37:13.774 --> 37:15.484
Megan Leavey.
Who's that?

37:16.277 --> 37:17.737
This is Chico.
Chico, sit.

37:19.822 --> 37:21.616
I trained Chico to
lick the enemy to death.

37:21.949 --> 37:23.075
(LAUGHS) Nice.

37:24.160 --> 37:26.162
So, where are you from?
New York.

37:26.662 --> 37:27.663
Ah, yeah? Me, too.

37:27.747 --> 37:29.874
You're not a Yankees fan,
though, right?

37:29.957 --> 37:30.957
Born and bred.

37:31.000 --> 37:32.084
Oh, come on.

37:32.501 --> 37:34.045
Dagger to my heart,
really?

37:34.670 --> 37:37.131
Well, I guess we'll
never speak again, Megan.

37:38.549 --> 37:40.676
Chico, we don't talk
to Yankees fans, right?

37:40.760 --> 37:41.886
Good boy.

37:47.308 --> 37:48.476
This is Corporal Morales.

37:48.851 --> 37:50.686
Morales,
Lance Corporal Leavey.

37:51.062 --> 37:52.438
Morales will drop you
at the ECP,

37:52.521 --> 37:54.690
then he's off to Sadr City,
so you'll be on your own

37:54.774 --> 37:56.168
till we can get
another team out there.

37:56.192 --> 37:58.444
Just try and keep your
dog from overheating.

37:58.694 --> 37:59.779
Okay.

38:00.321 --> 38:02.281
Last female handler
got her panties in a pretzel

38:02.365 --> 38:04.909
'cause we don't allow girls on
missions, just checkpoints.

38:05.159 --> 38:06.494
That gonna be
a problem with you?

38:06.577 --> 38:08.037
Not at all.
Good.

38:09.497 --> 38:10.873
Dismissed.

38:18.673 --> 38:20.007
"Panties in a pretzel."

38:20.800 --> 38:22.677
Hmm. (CHUCKLES)

38:24.011 --> 38:25.429
Thought we weren't
talking anymore.

38:26.597 --> 38:27.950
Well, I was talking
to myself right there,

38:27.974 --> 38:30.309
but, you know,
I'll give you another chance,

38:30.393 --> 38:32.313
and if you mention the
Yankees again, we're done.

38:34.522 --> 38:36.402
Staff Sergeant Jarvis
is a real charmer, though.

38:36.899 --> 38:39.026
Last week he told me
he always liked my people.

38:40.152 --> 38:41.988
My dad's Puerto Rican,
my mom's Scandinavian.

38:43.197 --> 38:44.877
Who do you think he was
talking about, huh?

38:45.199 --> 38:46.617
The Scandinavians,
obviously.

38:46.742 --> 38:48.302
Right, that's what I thought.
(CHUCKLES)

39:19.108 --> 39:20.568
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

39:47.595 --> 39:49.155
MORALES: Welcome
to the capital of shit.

39:50.473 --> 39:51.724
MEGAN:
What's with all the dogs?

39:51.807 --> 39:55.144
Strays, full of diseases.
Keep 'em away from your dog.

39:55.561 --> 39:56.771
Shoot 'em if you have to.

39:57.229 --> 39:58.522
Here's all you need to know.

39:58.606 --> 40:00.206
Don't search till
they're out of the car.

40:00.483 --> 40:01.817
Make sure they open
everything.

40:02.610 --> 40:04.445
Remember, Iraqis,
they don't like dogs.

40:04.904 --> 40:06.238
It's in their
religious teachings,

40:06.363 --> 40:07.723
and they damn sure
don't like ours.

40:07.782 --> 40:09.241
There's a bounty
on canine handlers

40:09.325 --> 40:11.577
and an even bigger bounty
on female canine handlers.

40:11.660 --> 40:14.163
Which means they'll
probably wanna kill you.

40:15.748 --> 40:17.428
Well, actually,
unless they wanna bone you.

40:17.666 --> 40:19.506
Or they might wanna bone you
and then kill you.

40:19.668 --> 40:22.296
And if one of them pulls out a
cell phone, boom, you're dead.

40:23.839 --> 40:25.674
Aside from that,
it's pretty chill.

40:27.009 --> 40:28.886
Seriously, be smart,

40:29.595 --> 40:31.515
keep your head on a swivel,
heightened awareness.

40:32.014 --> 40:33.057
Okay.

40:51.283 --> 40:53.536
Go, go, go,
get to the line.

41:07.716 --> 41:08.860
MORALES:
You need to have fun.

41:08.884 --> 41:09.964
DRIVER: No complaints, bro.

41:12.012 --> 41:13.389
MARINE: See ya.

41:16.142 --> 41:17.393
(DISTANT SHOUTING)

41:27.486 --> 41:28.904
MARINE: Hey,
keep everybody moving.

41:30.322 --> 41:31.824
Jones, move his truck.

41:33.617 --> 41:35.077
Rex, you want some water?

41:38.789 --> 41:40.749
MARINE: Bandini, tell that guy
to cut his engine.

41:41.208 --> 41:42.543
Turn your engine off.

41:42.751 --> 41:44.086
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

41:51.177 --> 41:53.262
Let's go, let's go,
let's go, let's go.

42:06.984 --> 42:08.527
Ask him the reason
for traveling today.

42:08.611 --> 42:10.112
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

42:10.404 --> 42:12.573
I'm heading to Baghdad
for business.

42:12.948 --> 42:14.325
You speak English.

42:14.408 --> 42:15.784
Yes, better for business.

42:16.493 --> 42:17.494
(ENGINE BACKFIRES)

42:17.786 --> 42:19.872
Hey! Cut your engine off.

42:20.456 --> 42:22.583
I told you to
turn that bike off.

42:22.791 --> 42:23.959
Lift your shirts.

42:24.084 --> 42:25.419
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

42:25.502 --> 42:28.130
Come on, turn around, come on.

42:31.926 --> 42:33.302
Leavey, clear the car.

42:33.636 --> 42:35.095
Open the trunk please, sir.

42:41.685 --> 42:42.686
(ENGINE BACKFIRES)

42:43.145 --> 42:44.647
MARINE: Jesus, Bandini.

42:45.147 --> 42:46.982
I told you to
turn that bike off.

42:48.150 --> 42:49.610
Get up, get up.

42:50.152 --> 42:51.779
Stand over here.
Lift your shirt.

42:51.862 --> 42:53.489
Damn straight,
better for business.

42:54.073 --> 42:55.115
Stay back.

42:57.284 --> 42:59.912
You want me to shoot you next time?
Pick your bike up.

43:02.122 --> 43:03.499
Don't touch it, though.

43:08.170 --> 43:09.338
No.

43:09.505 --> 43:10.756
(PANTING)

43:10.839 --> 43:12.800
Come here.

43:19.348 --> 43:20.724
(SNIFFING)

43:29.733 --> 43:30.943
Clear.

43:31.193 --> 43:32.695
What is his name?

43:32.778 --> 43:34.498
MARINE: Hey, kid,
we ask the questions here.

43:35.072 --> 43:37.592
Sir, could you get in the vehicle
and proceed to the checkpoint?

43:37.658 --> 43:39.285
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

43:46.542 --> 43:47.876
His name is Rex.

43:49.503 --> 43:50.504
FATHER: Here,

43:50.879 --> 43:53.799
let me give you
my card, X-box.

43:54.300 --> 43:55.426
MEGAN: No, no, no.

43:56.802 --> 43:58.637
Back in your vehicle now.
MEGAN: Rex!

43:59.388 --> 44:00.556
Come on.

44:02.766 --> 44:03.976
What are you doing?

44:04.059 --> 44:05.561
You never tell
a <i>Haji</i> your dog's name.

44:05.853 --> 44:06.853
He's just a kid.

44:06.895 --> 44:08.331
Yeah, and I've seen
kids not much older

44:08.355 --> 44:10.232
call a dog over with
a detonator in hand.

44:10.566 --> 44:13.027
You wanna keep your dog alive?
Sort your crap out.

44:13.694 --> 44:14.778
Hey, let's go.

44:15.863 --> 44:17.072
Next.

44:18.907 --> 44:21.201
Keep these people moving.
Let's go, let's go!

44:34.048 --> 44:36.342
We'll get better at this,
I promise.

44:38.010 --> 44:39.178
Good boy.

44:41.263 --> 44:43.015
Seek.
RECON GUY 1: You sure?

44:45.476 --> 44:46.745
RECON GUY 2: All right.
Oh, what is it?

44:46.769 --> 44:47.770
You did it.

44:48.395 --> 44:50.647
Good boy, good boy,
come on, come on.

44:51.023 --> 44:52.524
Seek, come on.

44:56.028 --> 44:57.388
Could be a full suit.
Check it out.

44:57.738 --> 44:59.823
MEGAN: Good boy, good boy.
Did he find it?

44:59.907 --> 45:01.200
Those guys ever take a break?

45:01.283 --> 45:03.118
No.
MEGAN: Come here.

45:03.827 --> 45:05.037
I guess so.

45:05.120 --> 45:06.288
MEGAN: Good boy.

45:06.622 --> 45:08.749
You wanna play, boy?
You wanna play? Go get it.

45:10.125 --> 45:11.919
Good boy, Rex.
Come here, Rex.

45:15.130 --> 45:16.298
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

45:16.590 --> 45:19.676
JARVIS: Leavey, Recon needs you
on a mission, five minutes.

45:26.100 --> 45:27.702
I thought I wasn't
allowed to go on missions.

45:27.726 --> 45:29.311
There's no one else.
Get your gear.

45:37.820 --> 45:38.904
Yo.

45:40.155 --> 45:42.875
They blew up five of our guys. Let's
get in there and smoke them out.

45:43.659 --> 45:45.744
One of you check the road.
The house is over here.

45:47.246 --> 45:48.766
I'll take the road.
You get the houses.

45:49.164 --> 45:52.167
Okay, hey, sweep the dogs.
They might be stuffed with IEDs.

46:08.517 --> 46:09.560
(SNIFFING)

46:14.857 --> 46:15.983
Clear.

46:24.992 --> 46:27.119
I just wish this
guy had a couple rugs.

46:27.911 --> 46:29.288
Ask him why so many rugs?

46:29.371 --> 46:30.706
They're prayer rugs.
Ask him.

46:31.123 --> 46:33.375
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

46:35.544 --> 46:36.920
They're a religious family.

46:37.296 --> 46:38.630
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

46:38.714 --> 46:40.090
They're not
enemies of the States.

46:40.215 --> 46:42.301
(CONTINUES IN ARABIC)

46:42.718 --> 46:43.987
And they thank
Americans for helping

46:44.011 --> 46:45.238
in the fight
against insurgents.

46:45.262 --> 46:47.306
Oh, we thank you
for your bullshit.

46:47.389 --> 46:49.308
Hey, open this cabinet.

46:49.558 --> 46:51.685
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

46:52.519 --> 46:53.937
Open it! (CONTINUES IN ARABIC)

46:57.065 --> 46:58.233
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

46:59.026 --> 47:00.652
Get back.

47:01.236 --> 47:02.446
(SNIFFING)

47:04.948 --> 47:06.217
RECON GUY: What's he got?
He got something?

47:06.241 --> 47:07.868
MEGAN: We need some room,
step back.

47:08.577 --> 47:09.661
Move these rugs.

47:09.745 --> 47:10.746
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

47:11.538 --> 47:12.915
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

47:14.666 --> 47:16.376
His sons put 'em there.
We don't care.

47:16.460 --> 47:17.836
Move them!
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

47:17.920 --> 47:18.962
He's not a well man.

47:19.046 --> 47:20.315
Tell <i>habibi</i> we don't
care about his health

47:20.339 --> 47:22.090
and he needs to move them.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

47:22.424 --> 47:23.842
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

47:24.092 --> 47:25.177
Move them now.

47:27.095 --> 47:28.263
RECON GUY: Today!

47:31.725 --> 47:33.393
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

47:38.232 --> 47:39.483
(SNIFFING RAPIDLY)

47:47.449 --> 47:49.826
Okay, gonna need someone to check that.
RECON GUY: I got it.

48:02.214 --> 48:03.465
Oh, my God.

48:03.799 --> 48:05.217
Don't move! Don't move!
(BARKING)

48:05.467 --> 48:06.802
Hey! Stop!

48:08.136 --> 48:09.137
Stop!

48:09.304 --> 48:10.722
Don't move! Don't move!

48:11.807 --> 48:14.309
RECON GUY 1: Nice work, cleared
out quicker than we found it.

48:15.477 --> 48:16.645
All right. More bad luck.

48:18.647 --> 48:19.815
MORALES: Look at this.

48:20.274 --> 48:21.650
This is you?

48:21.984 --> 48:23.110
Well, it's him.

48:23.652 --> 48:25.445
Well, don't get all
big-headed on me now.

48:27.155 --> 48:29.032
Shit, you just
saved a bunch of lives.

48:30.659 --> 48:32.828
Outstanding work.
Both of you.

48:34.204 --> 48:35.289
Thank you.

48:37.583 --> 48:39.167
Come on, Chico.

48:40.919 --> 48:42.796
(HIP HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

48:50.596 --> 48:52.014
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

48:54.266 --> 48:56.351
Three, two, one.

48:57.102 --> 48:58.186
You cheated!

48:59.229 --> 49:00.230
I won!

49:01.356 --> 49:02.899
I won! I won!

49:12.701 --> 49:14.536
It's okay, they're fine,
they're fine.

49:18.248 --> 49:19.875
(ALL WHOOPING)

49:33.722 --> 49:35.057
(ALL CHEERING)

49:36.183 --> 49:38.185
Yeah, we shook 'em up.
Chico.

49:39.394 --> 49:42.034
MORALES: Oh, you're slick, 'cause
I already know what card that is.

49:42.230 --> 49:43.690
There we go,
pick up some more.

49:43.982 --> 49:45.734
Keep going,
you still don't have it.

49:45.817 --> 49:46.818
Oh, my God.
Keep going.

49:46.902 --> 49:48.320
Keep going.
Relax.

49:48.403 --> 49:49.756
MORALES: He looks like he's
actually trying to decide

49:49.780 --> 49:51.823
which of my body parts
he wants to eat first.

49:51.907 --> 49:53.033
MEGAN: Yeah, he is.

49:53.241 --> 49:54.242
Oh!

49:54.743 --> 49:56.286
The moment has come.
Mmm-hmm.

49:56.787 --> 49:58.705
(GASPS)
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

50:00.499 --> 50:02.000
You set that up.

50:02.709 --> 50:04.044
Totally didn't.
(GROANS)

50:04.419 --> 50:05.962
That was good.
Thank you.

50:09.424 --> 50:10.592
So, Mets fan,

50:11.843 --> 50:13.011
did you ever play?

50:13.095 --> 50:15.681
I did, high school,
third base.

50:17.099 --> 50:18.850
I thought I was
actually pretty good,

50:19.393 --> 50:20.769
but college scouts disagreed,

50:21.687 --> 50:23.063
so here I am.

50:23.855 --> 50:27.609
Screw 'em, I'm not really a
sit-in-the-classroom kind of guy anyway.

50:28.193 --> 50:29.194
Me neither.

50:29.945 --> 50:32.114
So, what's your story?

50:32.489 --> 50:33.782
Why'd you join?

50:33.865 --> 50:36.201
I wanted to get the
fuck away from my life.

50:40.914 --> 50:42.124
That was a downer.

50:44.793 --> 50:47.295
Does it have
anything to do with Jesse?

50:49.756 --> 50:51.049
I saw your tattoo.

50:52.634 --> 50:53.635
Um...

50:56.388 --> 50:57.431
Yeah.

50:58.640 --> 50:59.933
I mean,
he was my best friend.

51:00.642 --> 51:02.362
We used to spend every
weekend at his house.

51:03.520 --> 51:04.789
I mean, not like that.
We were...

51:04.813 --> 51:05.897
He was like my brother.

51:05.981 --> 51:07.357
His family was amazing,

51:08.150 --> 51:09.317
unlike mine.

51:09.818 --> 51:11.153
I spent Christmases there,

51:12.654 --> 51:17.409
and one weekend we were
drinking and taking pills,

51:17.492 --> 51:20.162
doing stupid
high school stuff,

51:21.163 --> 51:24.624
and we took
the exact same amount.

51:24.708 --> 51:28.295
I mean, I probably took
even more than he did, but...

51:30.922 --> 51:33.300
Well, I woke up.
He didn't.

51:34.843 --> 51:40.098
His family keep trying to reach out,
but I can't even...

51:44.060 --> 51:45.740
It should have been me,
and we all know it.

51:52.027 --> 51:53.195
I gotta get up early.

51:55.030 --> 51:56.281
I'm gonna go to sleep.

52:02.454 --> 52:04.122
Good night.
MORALES: Night.

52:31.691 --> 52:35.695
Good boy, good boy.

52:49.751 --> 52:52.063
We need one dog team for a road
sweep and surrounding area check.

52:52.087 --> 52:53.213
But you requested
two teams.

52:53.296 --> 52:54.464
Things change.

52:54.548 --> 52:55.908
We only have
the room for one team.

52:58.093 --> 53:00.303
Hey, it's going down leash.
I'll go.

53:00.387 --> 53:01.429
BROWN: Leavey.

53:02.889 --> 53:04.182
I got this.

53:06.268 --> 53:07.352
BROWN: Line up!

53:07.435 --> 53:08.478
You heard him, let's go.

53:08.854 --> 53:10.146
Move it.

53:22.450 --> 53:23.660
GOMEZ: You're from New York?

53:23.743 --> 53:24.870
MEGAN: Yeah.

53:25.328 --> 53:26.746
Me, too.

53:27.956 --> 53:29.416
My first time in country.

53:33.003 --> 53:34.254
What about him?

53:35.630 --> 53:36.798
Germany.

53:37.173 --> 53:38.592
Germany.
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

53:38.675 --> 53:40.135
German shepherd,
I like that.

53:41.219 --> 53:42.387
You know what I heard?

53:42.971 --> 53:45.223
I heard the enemy likes
to steal the dogs, right?

53:45.307 --> 53:46.474
Strap bombs on them,

53:47.851 --> 53:49.269
send them back
to their owner.

53:50.061 --> 53:52.397
Well, since Rex can break
someone's arm with his teeth,

53:52.480 --> 53:53.607
I'm not too worried.

54:19.257 --> 54:20.675
Leavey, dog up.

54:23.970 --> 54:24.971
It's okay.

54:31.144 --> 54:32.687
(SNIFFING)

54:43.114 --> 54:45.274
MARINE 1: They've been spending
a lot of time together.

54:45.492 --> 54:46.677
MARINE 2:
I'm glad I'm not them.

54:46.701 --> 54:47.786
Stop talking!

55:30.370 --> 55:33.081
Good boy, good boy.

55:53.768 --> 55:55.228
Found something!

55:56.896 --> 55:59.524
Hey, Leavey, does he really
need another break?

56:00.525 --> 56:02.652
With all due respect,
it's been two hours,

56:02.736 --> 56:04.946
and it's 120 degrees,
so yeah, he does.

56:06.114 --> 56:07.434
It's not like
he hasn't earned it.

56:13.955 --> 56:15.540
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

56:18.877 --> 56:19.919
MEGAN:
Vehicle approaching.

56:20.003 --> 56:21.004
MARINE: Guns up.

56:25.133 --> 56:26.134
(REX BARKS)

56:28.887 --> 56:30.388
Rex.

56:33.183 --> 56:35.143
Gomez, warning shot,
one round.

56:37.479 --> 56:38.688
GOMEZ: He's not slowing.

56:39.147 --> 56:40.815
Stand by to light him up.

56:46.279 --> 56:47.280
(REX BARKS)

56:54.287 --> 56:55.663
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

56:57.040 --> 56:59.125
Gomez, O'Connor,
secure the <i>Haji.</i>

56:59.209 --> 57:00.794
Get on the ground,
get on the ground.

57:02.670 --> 57:04.172
Get on the ground.

57:06.007 --> 57:07.425
Get on the ground.

57:09.302 --> 57:12.305
Get on the ground now,
get on the ground.

57:12.388 --> 57:13.848
Lay flat on the ground now.

57:13.932 --> 57:15.076
Put your hands
behind your back.

57:15.100 --> 57:16.351
Hands behind your back.

57:18.853 --> 57:19.896
Rex!

57:20.522 --> 57:21.523
(REX PANTING)

57:22.315 --> 57:23.358
Clear!

57:23.525 --> 57:24.818
Leavey, check the vehicle.

57:25.610 --> 57:27.112
Hey, come on, let's go.

57:29.531 --> 57:30.990
Okay, okay.

58:01.646 --> 58:02.814
(GROANING)

58:08.903 --> 58:11.698
Rex, Rex!

58:12.782 --> 58:15.577
Rex, no, no, no.

58:26.462 --> 58:27.755
Rex.

58:36.389 --> 58:38.099
I'm not leaving
without my dog.

58:38.516 --> 58:40.351
MARINE: Come on, come on.

58:58.912 --> 58:59.996
BROWN: Hey!

59:00.163 --> 59:01.497
How did your dog miss that?

59:01.581 --> 59:02.874
You could have
got us all killed.

59:03.750 --> 59:06.044
GOMEZ: I never seen
an IED buried this deep.

59:09.881 --> 59:11.007
You gotta see this.

59:11.382 --> 59:13.426
They must have triggered
the bomb from those houses.

59:13.509 --> 59:15.303
I don't know, maybe
they were targeting Rex.

59:15.386 --> 59:16.864
BROWN: No, they were
targeting Leavey and Rex.

59:16.888 --> 59:18.073
GOMEZ:
Let's get those cowards.

59:18.097 --> 59:20.017
Radio Morales, get him and
his dog down here now.

59:20.058 --> 59:22.644
No, if we wait for Morales,
the spotters will be gone by then.

59:22.727 --> 59:24.395
We can do it.
No way, forget it.

59:24.479 --> 59:26.648
Do you see how many
IEDs we found today?

59:26.731 --> 59:28.334
How are you gonna make it
through the field without us?

59:28.358 --> 59:29.585
God damn it, Leavey,
you're injured.

59:29.609 --> 59:32.946
Yeah, because those assholes
waited all day watching us.

59:33.029 --> 59:34.256
CORPSMAN: She's got
a concussion, Sergeant.

59:34.280 --> 59:35.949
She may be confused,
disoriented.

59:36.032 --> 59:37.075
They almost killed us.

59:37.158 --> 59:40.286
How are you gonna make it through
the field and the house without us?

59:40.370 --> 59:41.955
What about your dog?
He's injured, too.

59:55.343 --> 59:56.386
He's fine.

59:57.845 --> 59:59.180
We can do this.

01:00:04.018 --> 01:00:05.019
Let's go!

01:00:05.103 --> 01:00:06.372
I'm gonna check
with Air Support.

01:00:06.396 --> 01:00:08.082
In the meantime, Gomez,
get your team together.

01:00:08.106 --> 01:00:09.774
Get in there, check it out,
do it fast.

